Sterling Bank has expressed optimism that it will start to pay dividend to its shareholders next year. The bank’s Chief Operating Officer (COO) Mr. Abubakar Suleiman, who stated this against the backdrop of non-payment of dividend to shareholders at the close of operation in 2018 at the 57 Annual General Meeting (AGM) held in Lagos, said that they had put measures in place to ensure the payment of dividend next year. “Your bank has provided strategy and by next year, we assure that the dividend will start to come,” he said.    Dividend warrants:  ‘Level of complaints traumatic’ SEC commences e-Dividend registration Zenith Bank to pay shareholders N87.9bn dividend